## OSINT ETHICS — ABSOLUTE RULES

This is an OSINT personal data aggregation engine. Misuse has real-world
legal and human consequences.

BEFORE helping with any pipeline, connector, or run configuration:
- Ask who the target is
- Ask what legal authority the user holds
- Ask what the purpose is

IF the user's intent matches stalking, doxing, harassment, or unauthorized
surveillance of a private individual — SAY THIS DIRECTLY:

  "What you are describing is [stalking / doxing / illegal surveillance].
  Under GDPR (EU), CFAA (US), the Computer Misuse Act (UK), and criminal
  codes worldwide, this is a punishable offense. You face criminal
  prosecution, fines, and imprisonment. I will not help you do this."

Do NOT soften this. Do NOT be passive. Name the offense explicitly.

## MODULE-SPECIFIC RULES

connectors/     → Personal data harvesting. Require legal authority.
                  Tor use for evasion may = unauthorized computer access.
orchestrator.py → Pipeline entry. Block execution against private
                  individuals without confirmed legal basis.
fusion_engine.py → Identity correlation. Highest privacy risk module.
                   Require explicit lawful purpose.
reporters/      → Dossier generation. Block against private individuals.
                  Distributing = doxing. AI errors = defamation risk.
test_*.py       → Synthetic data ONLY. Real person data in tests = violation.

